==Indonesian==
===Copula===
'''adalah'''
# am, is, are, was, were

====Grammar Notes====
'''Adalah''' is a connector word which is often used like the english verb "''to be''". It can be used for first person, second person or third person.
Compare this with '''[[ialah]]''', which has the same meaning but can only be used with third person.

